"{\"uid\": \"www.straitstimes.com.-opinion-brexit-poll-a-sobering-lesson-for-asia-Part1\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"If such a nation now wants to dig in its heels against these forces of globalisation, what of the rest of the world whose experience with the phenomenon is distinctly more contemporary?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 185, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The EU used to be held up as a model as we in Asia watched it expand from six nations to 10, then 12 and eventually 28 member states.\", \"from\": 187, \"to\": 320, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"With the exception of Greenland, which opted out as a Danish colony three decades ago but remains subject to EU treaties, no one had ever thought of quitting the union.\", \"from\": 321, \"to\": 489, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South-east Asian integration, which started in 1967, began with five nations grouped as Asean.\", \"from\": 491, \"to\": 585, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"This became six when Brunei joined in 1984 and has now grown to 10 members.\", \"from\": 586, \"to\": 661, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"South Asia, meanwhile, tried its own version, Saarc, albeit with less success.\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 740, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, the EU does not look so much like a winner anymore.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 797, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We have been made aware that there is no sure bet about the integration process being one-way.\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 892, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How did Britain come to this pass?\", \"from\": 894, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as it suited its purpose of ensuring that there was no concentration of power in Europe, say a Franco-German one, Britain went along with the widening of EU membership.\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Winston Churchill, the lionised wartime prime minister, even once called for a \\\"United States of Europe\\\".\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But now that it is obliged to accept immigrants from the other 27 members, including nations like Romania, it is clearly uneasy.\", \"from\": 1212, \"to\": 1340, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The sauce that was good for the British goose wasn't good for the British gander.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1422, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is a lesson here.\", \"from\": 1424, \"to\": 1447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As long as globalisation is about selling goods and products, no one complains too much, provided trade does not favour one party overwhelmingly.\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But once countries began to push for trade in services and free movement of labour, unease sets in.\", \"from\": 1594, \"to\": 1693, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And Britain is a net importer of goods and a net exporter of services.\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1764, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What the Brexit debate and vote has shown us is that we can never wish away primeval fears such as fear of being \\\"swamped by the other\\\".\", \"from\": 1766, \"to\": 1902, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When you combine these with economic realities such as stagnant wages and fears of reduced social welfare, you get an incendiary mix.\", \"from\": 1903, \"to\": 2036, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The exact pace of globalisation is hard to map, but Bulgarians, Romanians, Mexicans and, not to forget, Pakistanis and Indians, are easy to identify as villains of the show.\", \"from\": 2038, \"to\": 2211, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"To an extent, perhaps we in South-east Asia may have already tacitly acknowledged this reality - that some things just cannot be rushed.\", \"from\": 2213, \"to\": 2349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See how the language on an Asean Economic Community has changed.\", \"from\": 2350, \"to\": 2414, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Not too long ago, the pitch was about developing a single market and production base.\", \"from\": 2416, \"to\": 2501, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"These days, we seem happier with less-ambitious formulations such as striving for a \\\"highly integrated economy\\\".\", \"from\": 2502, \"to\": 2614, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"One lesson for Asia is how politics let loose can be the bane of social integration, with the potential to harm social compacts built up over decades.\", \"from\": 2616, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Last week, Singapore's Home Affairs and Law Minister K. Shanmugam took note of the anti-Muslim rhetoric in some Western nations arising from this.\", \"from\": 2767, \"to\": 2913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In a multiracial country, there is political profit in dividing people, playing on race, religion, stoking up fears.\", \"from\": 2914, \"to\": 3031, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is really unacceptable and I think morally reprehensible,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 3032, \"to\": 3102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The other cautionary tale, especially for significant nations such as China, India, Japan and Indonesia, is to go easy on nationalism.\", \"from\": 3104, \"to\": 3238, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In these days of fragmented loyalties, it may not be a bad thing to stress a national identity and character.\", \"from\": 3239, \"to\": 3348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But that's quite different from pushing an excessively nationalist agenda, which can be dangerous.\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3447, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Just look at the domestic, nationalistic pressures China has to contend with over the South China Sea disputes, which threaten to harden China's\", \"from\": 3449, \"to\": 3593, \"entities\": []}]}"